<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/498.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of
                                    Nicaragua</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua, Nicaragua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-25"><hi rend="italic">April
                                        25, 1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Peace signed day before yesterday, Amapala. I thank Your Excellency for
                            your great work toward achieving that happy result.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. S. Zelaya.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>